The number 2026 is at the point \((23,-22)\) of the square‑spiral.

For a lattice point \((x,y)\) let  

\[
r=\max(|x|,|y|), \qquad N_{\max}= (2r+1)^2 .
\]

\(N_{\max}\) is the number at the bottom‑right corner \((r,-r)\).  
For a point on the bottom edge \((x,-r)\)

\[
N = N_{\max}-(r-x).
\]

For the left edge \((-r,y)\)

\[
N = N_{\max}-(2r)-(y+r).
\]

For the top edge \((x,r)\)

\[
N = N_{\max}-(4r)-(x+r).
\]

For the right edge \((r,y)\)

\[
N = N_{\max}-(6r)-(r-y)= N_{\max}-(7r-y).
\]

---

### Position of 2026  

\(2026\) satisfies  

\[
(2\cdot23+1)^2 = 47^{2}=2209 >2026 \ge (2\cdot22+1)^2 =45^{2}=2025,
\]

so it lies in layer \(k=23\).  
The first number of this layer is at \((k,-k+1)=(23,-22)\). Hence \(2026\) is at \((23,-22)\).

---

